longest_values: This event will involve local youth in riding their bikes along two main East Harlem streets to raise public awareness about the impact of and alternatives to youth-on-youth violence. It will be followed by a street fair that will feature information on local programs that engage youth and protect them from violece.

It will support eight boat rides along the park, Clinton Music Series of eight free concerts in Clinton Cove Park and at Pier 84, and the photography program for public school teenagers in order to attract people to the Park, educate them about it and provide them with recreation.

The West 135th Street Block Association, Inc. is requesting funds to beautify the blocks.  Our plan is to decorate each tree during the Christmas holiday.  Second, we will use the funds awarded to us to plant flowers and Evergreen trees in every pit in the summer.

The Downtown Boathouse runs the largest free kayaking program in the world. Our Equipment Replenishment Project invests in essential equipment needed to support the growing number of participants and to continue providing safe access to the water.
